                   "message":  "GLB-WATCHER-CREATE-EVENT: hot-reload on rename-replace (Create) saves\n\nLands a previously-uncommitted, test-backed local change (human-authorized\nsalvage, dispatch 2 of 2).\n\nThe --glb hot-reload watcher converted only notify::EventKind::Modify(_) events\non the active glb_source_path into reload intent. A user save frequently lands\nas a rename-replace (write temp, rename over the target), which the OS reports\nas a Create event for the target path -- so those saves were missed (no hot\nreload). Widen the filter to accept Create(_) too, catching both\nstraight-overwrite (Modify) and rename-replace (Create) sequences. Sibling and\nRemove/Access/Other events stay ignored; the debounce window is unchanged.\n\neditor/rge-editor/src/glb_watcher.rs:\n- event_targets_path(): match Modify(_) | Create(_) at the target path.\n- module doc + predicate rustdoc updated (\"a filesystem write landing at the\n  active --glb path\").\n- test import adds CreateKind; new create_event_for() helper + test\n  event_filter_accepts_create_on_target.\n\nNo new dependency (CreateKind is from the already-used notify::event). Single\nfile; 0 Cargo.toml.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (new + existing filter tests pass);\ncargo check --all-targets clean (no new warnings); nightly fmt clean.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
